--> terraform provisioner
Terraform Provisioner is used to execute scripts or commands on a local machine or remote server after a resource is created or destroyed.

Types of Provisioners
1️⃣ local-exec
Runs commands on your local machine.
Example:

resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  ami           = "ami-0abcdef1234567890"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  provisioner "local-exec" {
    command = "echo Instance Created"
  }
}
When the instance is created in Amazon EC2, it prints:

Instance Created

2️⃣ remote-exec
Runs commands inside the created server.
Example:

resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  ami           = "ami-0abcdef1234567890"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  provisioner "remote-exec" {
    inline = [
      "sudo apt update",
      "sudo apt install nginx -y"
    ]
  }
}
This installs **Nginx on the EC2 instance.

3️⃣ file provisioner
Copies files from your machine to the server.  [local to remote]
Example:

provisioner "file" {
  source      = "app.sh"
  destination = "/home/ubuntu/app.sh"
}


